node.text:
I want you to fast-forward to you at 80 years old. Look at your hands, see the wrinkles etched in your waxy skin. Now, as that 80 year old I want you to look back at your life with two scenarios.

1. You played it safe. You worked the corporate job, and most nights when you got home you drank a bottle of wine to forget about it. You settled for the comfortable relationship, put on a bit too much weight, and started having sex less and less. You watched a lot of Netflix, were often afraid of getting sick, but all in all you did alright for yourself. 

2. You went for it. A full send to life. You quit your corporate job to follow your passion and contribute your gifts to the world. Your life was filled with adventure and mystery. You failed often, but your triumphs were glorious. You were friends with rogues, scoundrels, saints and geniuses. You trained yourself to overcome your fears, and lived a life of freedom and sovereignty. 

If you prefer scenario 2, then I wrote Go For Your Win for you. Because I prefer scenario 2 and I wrote Go For Your Win for my own younger self. It's every piece of advice I have to offer, updated and revised for this latest course release. 

Click the link in bio or head to AubreyMarcus.com/GoForYourWin to learn more

#gfyw #goforyourwin #personaldevelopment #challengeaccepted

In order to stretch our capacities and grow as humans, we are required to do things we haven’t yet done.

#impostersyndrome #personalgrowth #trusttheprocess

🎥 by @maxwmccoy
🎶 "Remember Jah" by the incredible @satsang

node.text:
Awaken King
Rise Rise Rise
From the long slumber
Disrobe the tattered 
threads of comparison
Evacuate the dilapidation 
of conditioned identity
Cloak yourself 
in the chrysanthemum 
of consciousness
Trade your fractured mind 
for fractal spirit

Awaken Queen
This is your time
You must rise and reign
Show people to love
Show people to cry
Show people to dance
Show people to play
Remind people 
That there are no people
Who are not part 
of the Universal steeple
That houses God

Left right
Black white
Red blue
False true
American
Afghan

What happens 
If the polarities unite
Get over the fight
Step over the pain
Of right and wrong
And sing the sacred song
Of who we really are
To those who have forgotten the words

#unitedpolarity 🤞

Art: L. roche | Mushroom Dreams

node.text:
When you wish death upon someone in the name of saving life.

When you beat someone bloody in the name of their health.

When you mandate that a child risks their future to make you feel safer.

When medical professionals are silenced in the name of ‘science’ - the process of testing and challenging hypotheses.

Something else is at work. A darker thing, lying in the shadow of your psyche. Your fear turned to rage and projected externally. Subconsciously believing that the solution to what you feel inside, lies in the destruction of the Other. This has been the sentiment at the root of countless atrocities. With pitchforks, fire, and now with pixels.

I pray that we do not repeat our sordid history. I pray that we stop dehumanizing ALL people, and instead choose reverence. 

There are no ‘sheep’. There are no ‘unclean’ domestic terrorists. There are humans making the best choices they can with the information they have been exposed to and their intuition. 

Left, right
Red, blue,
Vaxxed, unvaxxed.

We’re all on the same team. A human team, part of the Earth team, part of the divine team, and our team needs us. Shall we fight amongst ourselves until our planet burns? Will righteousness be a comforting blanket when the oceans die and the crops fail? 

If humans are the problem, humans are also the solution. We need each other. Please, please, I pray we wake up before it is too late. I want my children and their children to dive off waterfalls, go to the Louvre, dive in the barrier reef.

We’ll never get there unless we come together. It’s okay to fight for what you believe in, we need to stand for our truth, but may we never forget that behind the beliefs of another is a soul just like ours.

It is time to end the violent desire for homogeneity and unite the polarity by remembering our humanity. 

This is what I stand for. If you feel this too, use the hashtag #unitedpolarity and let’s make it a movement 💚🤞

node.text:
Our mind is a computer that is overworked, overheated, with too many tabs open, software waiting to download, and the cooling fan just can't keep up. Touching infinity is like hitting the reset button. Where for one moment the mind collapses into GOD. And that moment is timeless, and eternal. It is everything that ever was, and ever could be. Then when you reboot the computer, everything runs much more smoothly.

There are a lot of ways to touch infinity. Breathwork, plant medicine, ecstatic dance, floatation tanks, can all get you there. It doesn't matter how, it just matters that you find your own way 🤎. 

#resetyourmind #overthinking #biohacking

node.text:
I want you to fast-forward to you at 80 years old. Look at your hands, see the wrinkles etched in your waxy skin. Now, as that 80 year old I want you to look back at your life with two scenarios.

1. You played it safe. You worked the corporate job, and most nights when you got home you drank a bottle of wine to forget about it. You settled for the comfortable relationship, put on a bit too much weight, and started having sex less and less. You watched a lot of Netflix, were often afraid of getting sick, but all in all you did alright for yourself. 

2. You went for it. A full send to life. You quit your corporate job to follow your passion and contribute your gifts to the world. Your life was filled with adventure and mystery. You failed often, but your triumphs were glorious. You were friends with rogues, scoundrels, saints and geniuses. You trained yourself to overcome your fears, and lived a life of freedom and sovereignty. 

If you prefer scenario 2, then I wrote Go For Your Win for you. Because I prefer scenario 2 and I wrote Go For Your Win for my own younger self. It's every piece of advice I have to offer, updated and revised for this latest course release. 

Click the link in bio or head to AubreyMarcus.com/GoForYourWin to learn more

#gfyw #goforyourwin #personaldevelopment #challengeaccepted

First time back on the hardwood in a decade 🤩. Basketball was one of the most meaningful things in my life for a good 20 years. It was great to hear the shoes squeak and the whistles blow in the gym again.

And I had fans! Of course it was just my wife @vylanamarcus and my framily @sorayayd and @ev.thecreator but it was epic.
